<p>I am coding a reddit bot and need something to happen at a certain time, on a certain day. I can manually program the dates in. Here is what I have so far: </p>  <pre><code>import os import time  import praw  r = praw.Reddit(user_agent='redditbot 0.1 by /u/NGTmeaty')  r.login(os.environ['REDDIT_USER'], os.environ['REDDIT_PASS'])  while True:     nstr = now.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")     if nstr == "2015-9-23 19:39:0.000000":         r.submit('NFLStreams_Private', 'Redskins Game!',              text='Test Please post any streams for the redskins game in here!')      if nstr == "2015-9-24 20:25:0.000000":           r.submit('NFLStreams_Private', 'Redskins Game!',              text='Please post any streams for the redskins game in here!')      time.sleep(30) </code></pre>  <p><strong>update:</strong></p>  <p>My new code is</p>  <pre><code>import os import time import praw   r = praw.Reddit(user_agent='redditbot 0.1 by /u/NGTmeaty')  r.login(os.environ['REDDIT_USER'], os.environ['REDDIT_PASS'])  while True:      nstr = now.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")      if nstr.startswith('2015-9-26 13:38'):          r.submit('NFLStreams_Private', 'Redskins Game!',             text='Test Please post any streams for the redskins game in here!')  </code></pre>